Having regard to the character of this Litany, and tho circumstance that it is found in a generalized and slightly modified form in the Ely Pontifical in the library of Trinity Collega described below, in immediate connection with the Coronatiou Office, and lastly, to the prominence given in it to Matilda‚I am led to think that it is the Litany sung at the coronatiou of Matilda by Archbishop Aldred in 1068.
